N.J. Nicholas Jr., president and chiefoperating officer of Time Inc, told security analysts thecompany is now engaged in talks to join a consortium of cablecompanies that will invest in Cable News Network.    Nicholas declined to give any details, but said anannouncement might be ready in a few days. He also declined tosay whether the investment would be made by Time Inc orAmerican Television and Communications Corp, a public companyin which Time owns a majority stake.    Cable News Network is owned by Turner Broadcasting System&lt;TBS>. Reuter&#3;